Elementalist 53th Season <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ucieloinfierno.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Cielo Infierno</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 5<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(6/18/02 12:40:47 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm44.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=64.topic&index=28>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Mages...</span><hr size=1> Mages are a great class! My mage is only 46, so I can't speak to how she is treated or used in the high end game, but right now, she is extremely useful.<br>
<br>
If you think about it, a mage can make every member of the party better in some fashion, contributing much more to the the success of the group than many would imagine.<br>
<br>
For example:<br>
<br>
I was invited on a Kedge raid a few weeks ago. At the meeting spot, I created waterstones, lev rings, and focus items for everyone that could use them. The clerics each having a mana cost reduction and shortened casting time item, making them able to cast more heals at a much faster rate. All casters were equipped with at least a damage bracer (which they love me for <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  ), obviously allowing them to cause more damage to the mob.  Once inside the zone, I summoned weapons for pets, arrows for pullers, and food for someone who had just run out. When the fighting began, all tanks were DSed, I sent my pet on the appropriate mob, malised and nuked  them at the proper times.<br>
<br>
So, now what do we have? The mage has contributed to every aspect of the group. Her arrows are safely pulling the mobs, and when the mob attacks the puller, the mob takes DS damage. As the melees are attacking, the nukers are hitting for more damage based on the damage bracer, and getting less resist based on the mage's malise. The person that was out of food is now sustained and able to regenerate mana. Without the food, they would have wound up almost a useless member. Eveyone's pets are hitting harder.There is also that extra tank AND nuker tossed into the mix (mage's fire pet), wearing DS that is doing about 36 damage with every hit. This pet can also allow the tank a breather, taking stress off of the cleric.The cleric is keeping the tanks healthy because she is conserving mana, and casting heals quicker, thus allowing there to be more pulls quicker, everyone getting more xp or loot in the end, improving the overall success of the endeavor.<br>
<br>
See how that works? Mages &gt; All <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
I guess if I had a tip to give you, it would be to get very good at pet control. I have all of my commands hotkeyed along with a message that lets my group know what I am doing. Pet control IS a bit easier now, as they have changed them to not aggro everything, and not attack mezzed mobs, but it is still important in many cases.<br>
<br>
I hope that made sense :/ <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ukiyatmarik.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kiya TMarik</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Fisher Gal</span><br>  Posts: 57<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(6/18/02 1:30:46 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm44.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=64.topic&index=29>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Mages...</span><hr size=1> Great post Cielo. This is very interesting for those of us who are not so familiar with the abilities of the Magician. I envy the class sometimes... <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><i><b><a href="http://www.geocities.com/kiyafv/">Kiya T`Marik<a/></b></i> - <font size="1"><a href="http://www.geocities.com/theindigovoid/">Indigo Void</a> - FV<br>
