I'd never played a mage before, thus i picked it to play on test Firiona vie. I liked it, so when server went live, i remade the same class/name and have been there since. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><img src=http://selquar.travelersrealm.com/gensig1.gif></img>
<a Href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=130634>My Gear</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uyanaripethugger.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Yanari Pethugger</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(10/16/02 10:36:49 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm44.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=64.topic&index=39>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Low to medium level mages are excellent in 2-member groups.</span><hr size=1> Hullo,<br>
<br>
I've been out and about on the world of Norrath for about 3 months now.  <br>
What I've noticed is that there are quite a few mages, but they indeed get to solo a lot (not always by choice).<br>
<br>
Now, I found it's easy to make friends, maybe also because my personality is such that I'm easy to get along with.  I help out whenever I can, be it giving new players my spare coppers/silvers I'm carrying, or summoning them a set of armour/weapons/food/drink/bandaids/...<br>
<br>
The friends I've made were usually people LFG.  <br>
They run around alone, and being a mage, soloing, you tend to get lonely and look for conversation.  <br>
You Hail them,  or send them a tell and ask if they might want to join up with a mage... since they are LFG and haven't had any luck, they'll most certainly give you a try.  This is where you get to prove yourself, and it's easy...<br>
<br>
You need to know about combat, how to assist, and when or when not to nuke - once you get to mid-20's you should have figured it out, if not, quit playing EQ ( :-p ).<br>
<br>
Summon your bags of weapons and armour, show them the stats, sometimes you provide them with a better item while it is only still just summoned... be it AC-wise, other stats-wise, ...<br>
Offer them food/drink/bandages (they only cost you mana).<br>
They'll be happy, since it didni cost them a thing.<br>
<br>
Anyhow, in my experience I've worked with Shadowknights, Clerics and Enchanters...<br>
Enchanterpets can also use your summoned weapons and armour, same for SK-pets... (though they tend to refrain from using them when grouped).<br>
<br>
So, there you are, being the second tank (well, your pet at least).  Fighting starts, the tank goes looking for a mob (or yourself)... then bring it in, you DS the tank (and your pet), Malise the mob, cancel magic it if need be, then wait and see how the tank(s) are doing, nuke when necessary...  At this pont, an enchanter can nuke along, it can buff the pets, it can mesmerize adds, ...<br>
<br>
The shadowknight (wether or not they have pets) can now back off easily and drain life or leech or whatever it is they do, since your pet is tanking the mob, it can fear adds, snare the one mob your pet is still fighting, ...<br>
The Cleric has buffed your pet, you've DS'd it and now both of you can sit down and relax, heal the pet in turns, or nuke in turns...<br>
<br>
Warriors can use the DS too, they can be bandaged by you and themselves, since you nuke along with warriors the critter goes down more easily, tank and pet keeping the aggro...<br>
<br>
All in all, groups for mages are, imho, best when just two persons are in the group.<br>
<br>
Now as far as high-level encounters go, I've only reached the 42nd level of summoning there is, and it's getting tougher to solo while 2-person groups still work best in my opinion (I've not died in such a group, ever, and only twice so far has the person in my group bitten the dust).  And I've been playing like this since lvl 20-something.<br>
<br>
So, groups, naah, just pick out the one person who's LFG... you'll make a killer combo team... the pet can always be sic'ed on a second mob (though mostly it's useful to just kill the mobs in the order they come).<br>
<br>
Anyhow, just my 2cp - but try it out, target the ones LFG, talk to them and they WILL guve you a chance and they WILL love it... (if ofcourse you play well, not going berserk like I've seen some mages do).<br>
<br>
Take care, see you in game,<br>
<br>
Yanari Pethugger, lover of elementals, summoner of sorts, 10th circle, 42nd level in all.<br>
Member of the Gnomish Allliance of Gnomes.<br>
